Name: Description
OM-class: An object containing all the parameters needed to control the MSE which can be build from component Stock, Fleet and Obs objects. Almost all of these inputs are a vector of length 2 which describes the upper and lower bounds of a uniform distribution from which to sample the parameter.

Name: Function call
OM-class: Objects can be created by calls of the form new('OM', Stock, Fleet, Obs, Imp) .

Name: Name
OM-class: Name of the operating model

Name: nsim
OM-class: The number of simulations

Name: proyears
OM-class: The number of projected years

Name: nyears
OM-class: The number of years for the historical simulation

Name: maxage
OM-class: The maximum age of individuals that is simulated (there is no 'plus group': individuals die off beyone the maximum age so there isn't a huge cost to simulating more older age classes)

Name: R0
OM-class: The magnitude of unfished recruitment. This is normally fixed to some arbitrary value since it simply scales the simulated numbers)

Name: M
OM-class: Natural mortality rate (uniform distribution)

Name: Msd
OM-class: Inter-annual variability in natural mortality rate expressed as a coefficient of variation (uniform distribution)

Name: Mgrad
OM-class: Mean temporal trend in natural mortality rate, expressed as a percentage change in M per year (uniform distribution)

Name: h
OM-class: Steepness of the stock recruit relationship (uniform distribution)

Name: SRrel
OM-class: Type of stock-recruit relationship (1)Beverton-Holt (2) Ricker

Name: Linf
OM-class: Maximum length (uniform distribution)

Name: K
OM-class: von B. growth parameter k (uniform distribution)

Name: t0
OM-class: von B. theoretical age at length zero (uniform distribution)

Name: Ksd
OM-class: Inter-annual variability in growth parameter k (uniform distribution)

Name: Kgrad
OM-class: Mean temporal trend in growth parameter k, expressed as a percentage change in k per year (uniform distribution)

Name: Linfsd
OM-class: Inter-annual variability in maximum length - uniform distribution

Name: Linfgrad
OM-class: Mean temporal trend in maximum length, expressed as a percentage change in Linf per year (uniform distribution)

Name: recgrad
OM-class: Mean temporal trend in log-normal recruitment deviations (uniform distribution)

Name: AC
OM-class: Autocorrelation in recruitment deviations rec(t)=AC*rec(t-1)+(1-AC)*sigma(t) (uniform distribution)

Name: a
OM-class: Length-weight parameter alpha (uniform distribution)

Name: b
OM-class: Length-weight parameter beta (uniform distribution)

Name: D
OM-class: Current level of stock depletion (Bcurrent/Bunfished) (uniform distribution)

Name: Size_area_1
OM-class: The size of area 1 relative to area 2 (uniform distribution)

Name: Frac_area_1
OM-class: The fraction of the unfished biomass in stock 1 (uniform distribution)

Name: Prob_staying
OM-class: The probability of inviduals in area 1 remaining in area 1 over the course of one year

Name: beta
OM-class: A parameter controlling hyperstability/hyperdepletion. I^beta therefore values below 1 lead to hyperstability (an index that decreases slower than true abundance) and values above 1 lead to hyperdepletion (an index that decreases more rapidly than true abundance)(uniform distribution)

Name: Spat_targ
OM-class: Distribution of fishing in relation to spatial biomass: F is proportional to B^Spat_targ (uniform distribution)

Name: LFS
OM-class: Shortest length that is fully vulnerable to fishing (uniform distribution)

Name: L5
OM-class: Shortest length at 5 percent vulnerability (uniform distribution)

Name: Vmaxlen
OM-class: The vulnerability of the longest (oldest) fish (uniform distribution)

Name: SelYears
OM-class: Vector of verticies that index years where historical selectivity pattern changed. Leave empty to ignore

Name: AbsSelYears
OM-class: vector of absolute year values that correspond to year indices in SelYears. Used only for plotting

Name: L5Lower
OM-class: Optional vector of values of length SelYears, specifiying lower limits of L5 (use  ChooseSelect   function to set these. Overrides L5 above)

Name: L5Upper
OM-class: Optional vector of values of length SelYears, specifiying upper limits of L5 (use  ChooseSelect   function to set these. Overrides L5 above)

Name: LFSLower
OM-class: Optional vector of values of length SelYears, specifiying lower limits of LFS (use  ChooseSelect   function to set these. Overrides LFS above)

Name: LFSUpper
OM-class: Optional vector of values of length SelYears, specifiying upper limits of LFS (use  ChooseSelect   function to set these. Overrides LFS above)

Name: VmaxLower
OM-class: Optional vector of values of length SelYears, specifiying lower limits of Vmaxlen (use  ChooseSelect   function to set these. Overrides Vmaxlen above)

Name: VmaxUpper
OM-class: Optional vector of values of length SelYears, specifiying upper limits of Vmaxlen (use  ChooseSelect   function to set these. Overrides Vmaxlen above)

Name: isRel
OM-class: Are the selectivity parameters relative to size-of-maturity? TRUE or FALSE

Name: L50
OM-class: Length at 50 percent maturity (uniform distribution)

Name: L50_95
OM-class: Length increment from 50 to 95 percent maturity (uniform distribution)

Name: Esd
OM-class: Inter-annual variability in fishing mortality rate

Name: EffYears
OM-class: Vector of verticies, years at which to simulate varying relative effort

Name: EffLower
OM-class: Lower bound on relative effort corresponding to EffYears (uniform distribution)

Name: EffUpper
OM-class: Uppper bound on relative effort corresponding to EffYears (uniform distribution)

Name: qinc
OM-class: Average percentage change in fishing efficiency (uniform distribution)(applicable only to forward projection and input controls)

Name: qcv
OM-class: Inter-annual variability in fishing efficiency (uniform distribution)(applicable only to forward projection and input controls)

Name: CurrentYr
OM-class: The current calendar year (final year) of the historical simulations (e.g. 2011)

Name: Cobs
OM-class: Log-normal catch observation error expressed as a coefficient of variation (uniform distribution)

Name: Cbiascv
OM-class: A coefficient of variation controlling the sampling of bias in catch observations for each simulation (uniform distribution)

Name: CAA_nsamp
OM-class: Number of catch-at-age observation per time step (uniform distribution)

Name: CAA_ESS
OM-class: Effective sample size (independent age draws) of the multinomial catch-at-age observation error model (uniform distribution)

Name: CAL_nsamp
OM-class: Number of catch-at-length observation per time step (uniform distribution)

Name: CAL_ESS
OM-class: Effective sample size (independent length draws) of the multinomial catch-at-length observation error model (uniform distribution)

Name: CALcv
OM-class: Lognormal, variability in the length at age (uniform distribution)

Name: Iobs
OM-class: Observation error in the relative abundance indices expressed as a coefficient of variation (uniform distribution)

Name: Perr
OM-class: The extent of inter-annual log-normal recruitment variability (sigma R)(uniform distribution)

Name: Period
OM-class: Period for cylical recruitment pattern in years (uniform distribution). Leave empty to ignore

Name: Amplitude
OM-class: Amplitude in deviation from long-term average recruitment during recruitment cycle, both positive and negative (uniform distribution). E.g., a range from 0 to 0.5 means recruitment decreases or increases by up to 50% each cycle. Leave empty to ignore

Name: Mcv
OM-class: Persistent bias in the prescription of natural mortality rate sampled from a log-normal distribution with coefficient of variation (Mcv)(uniform distribution)

Name: Kcv
OM-class: Persistent bias in the prescription of growth parameter k sampled from a log-normal distribution with coefficient of variation (Kcv)(uniform distribution)

Name: t0cv
OM-class: Persistent bias in the prescription of t0 sampled from a log-normal distribution with coefficient of variation (t0cv)(uniform distribution)

Name: Linfcv
OM-class: Persistent bias in the prescription of maximum length sampled from a log-normal distribution with coefficient of variation (Linfcv)(uniform distribution)

Name: LFCcv
OM-class: Persistent bias in the prescription of lenght at first capture sampled from a log-normal distribution with coefficient of variation (LFCcv)(uniform distribution)

Name: LFScv
OM-class: Persistent bias in the prescription of length-at-fully selection sampled from a log-normal distribution with coefficient of variation (LFScv)(uniform distribution)

Name: B0cv
OM-class: Persistent bias in the prescription of maximum lengthunfished biomass sampled from a log-normal distribution with coefficient of variation (B0cv)(uniform distribution)

Name: FMSYcv
OM-class: Persistent bias in the prescription of FMSY sampled from a log-normal distribution with coefficient of variation (FMSYcv)(uniform distribution)

Name: FMSY_Mcv
OM-class: Persistent bias in the prescription of FMSY/M sampled from a log-normal distribution with coefficient of variation (FMSY_cv)(uniform distribution)

Name: BMSY_B0cv
OM-class: Persistent bias in the prescription of BMsY relative to unfished sampled from a log-normal distribution with coefficient of variation (BMSY_B0cv)(uniform distribution)

Name: rcv
OM-class: Persistent bias in the prescription of intrinsic rate of increase sampled from a log-normal distribution with coefficient of variation (rcv)(uniform distribution)

Name: LenMcv
OM-class: Persistent bias in the prescription of length at 50 percent maturity sampled from a log-normal distribution with coefficient of variation (A50cv)(uniform distribution)

Name: Dbiascv
OM-class: Persistent bias in the prescription of stock depletion sampled from a log-normal distribution with coefficient of variation (Linfcv)(uniform distribution)

Name: Dcv
OM-class: Imprecision in the prescription of stock depletion among years, expressed as a coefficient of variation (uniform distribution)

Name: Btbias
OM-class: Persistent bias in the prescription of current stock biomass sampled from a uniform-log distribution with range (Btbias)(uniform distribution)

Name: Btcv
OM-class: Imprecision in the prescription of current stock biomass among years expressed as a coefficient of variation (uniform distribution)

Name: Fcurbiascv
OM-class: Persistent bias in the prescription of current fishing mortality rate sampled from a log-normal distribution with coefficient of variation (Fcurcv)(uniform distribution)

Name: Fcurcv
OM-class: Imprecision in the prescription of current fishing mortality rate among years expressed as a coefficient of variation (uniform distribution)

Name: hcv
OM-class: Persistent bias in steepness (uniform distribution)

Name: Icv
OM-class: Observation error in realtive abundance index expressed as a coefficient of variation (uniform distirbution)

Name: maxagecv
OM-class: Bias in the prescription of maximum age (uniform distribution)

Name: Reccv
OM-class: Bias in the knowledge of recent recruitment strength (uniform distribution)

Name: Irefcv
OM-class: Bias in the knowledge of the relative abundance index at BMSY (uniform distribution)

Name: Brefcv
OM-class: Bias in the knowledge of BMSY (uniform distribution)

Name: Crefcv
OM-class: Bias in the knowledge of MSY(uniform distribution)

Name: cpars
OM-class: A list of custom parameters (single parameters are a vector nsim long, time series are a matrix nsim rows by nyears columns)

Name: seed
OM-class: A random seed to ensure users can reproduce results exactly

Name: Source
OM-class: A reference to a website or article form which parameters were taken to define the operating model

Name: TACSD
OM-class: lognormal standard deviation in fraction of TAC taken (uniform distribution)

Name: TACFrac
OM-class: Mean fraction of TAC taken (uniform distribution) (can be an improper fraction greater than 1)

Name: ESD
OM-class: lognormal standard deviation in fraction of TAE taken(uniform distribution)

Name: EFrac
OM-class: Mean fraction of recommended effort taken (uniform distribution)

Name: SizeLimSD
OM-class: lognormal error in size limit implementation (uniform distribution)

Name: SizeLimFrac
OM-class: Mean fraction of the size limit (uniform distribution) (can be an improper fraction greater than 1)

Name: DiscMort
OM-class: Discard mortality rate (uniform distribution) (can be an improper fraction greater than 1)
